European foulbrood of honey bees, Sweden
----------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 26 Aug 2015 from Dr Ingrid Eilertz, Chief Veterinary Officer Director and Head, Swedish Board of Agriculture Department for Animal Welfare and Health, Ministry for Rural Affairs, Jonkoping, Sweden

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 29 Jul 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 30 Jul 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2012
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Melissococcus plutonius_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Orebro, Vivalla, Orebro, Orebro Lan
Date of start of the outbreak: 29 Jul 2015
Outbreak status: resolved 30 Jul 2015
Epidemiological unit: apiary
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Bees (hives) / 1 / 1 / - / - / -
Affected population: Dead larvae were found in combs among otherwise healthy larvae.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Bees (hives) / 100 / ** / ** / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Swedish University of Agriculture Sciences (national laboratory) / Bees / bacteriological examination / 30 Jul 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak in the centre of Sweden can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

